# search for mountain of highest peak# there should be just 1 mountain# both sides should have equal height#height must be odd a=int(input())z=list(map(int,input().split()))  ans=[]cnt=1for i in range(1,len(z)):    if(z[i]>z[i-1]):        if(i==1):            cnt+=1            trend=1            continue;                         if(trend==1):            cnt+=1        else:            ans.append([cnt,0])            cnt=2            trend=1     else:        if(i==1):            cnt+=1            trend=0            continue;         if(trend==0):            cnt+=1        else:            ans.append([cnt,1])            cnt=2            trend=0            from collections import *ans.append([cnt,trend])dl=defaultdict(int)maxa=0for i in range(len(ans)):    dl[ans[i][0]]+=1    maxa=max(maxa,ans[i][0]) if(dl[maxa]==2 and maxa%2==1):    flag=0    for i in range(len(ans)-1):        if(ans[i][0]==ans[i+1][0] and ans[i][0]==maxa and ans[i][1]==1):            flag=1            break;     if(flag==1):        print('1')        exit(0)print(0)                
